Section : Preparation (20) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
1.Prepare test unit and ensure it is the latest preload image and BIOS version.
2.Enable hibernate function. --> Control Panel -->Hardware and Sound -->Power Options -->Choose what the power button does --> Change settings that are currently unavailable.
3.Install test tools: DPTF/AMD system deck and 3DMark tool.
4.If the project supports intel CPU OC, please download the latest version of intel XTU Tool (https://www.intel.cn/content/www/cn/zh/download/17881/intel-extreme-tuning-utility-intel-xtu.html)
Notice: This case is only for Lenovo Y series. Please omit this case if your platform not support Fn+Q function.
Note: Below function only supportted by shipping and "Work with limitation" Adapter. 1. Performance Mode. 2. Custom Mode. 3. dGPU hotplug AUTO Mode - dGPU re-install by insert AC.
 
Section : Mode Switch Check (400) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Fn+Q
1. Launch Vantage/Legion Space/Legion Zone thermal mode UI in AC and check "Fn+Q" status, keep Vantage/Legion Space/Legion Zone UI open. For FN+Q 7.0 and Later: 1).FN+Q 7.0 and Later will not be linked to the Power Plan, so the Power Plan does not need to be checked. 2).Verify that the OS Power mode is Balanced by default
Make sure the default status should be Balance mode both AC and DC mode. Power LED is white,system power plan is Legion Balance mode. *Note: Legion power plan only applies for legacy S3 system. Power plan is Balanced for the Modern standby system as default. (the same below). For FN+Q7.0: OS Power Mode:Balanced.The Power Plan does not change.
2. Press Fn+Q hotkey to switch Thermal mode. Note:FN+Q 7.0 and Later will not be linked to the Power Plan, so the Power Plan does not need to be checked.
Make sure there are three mode Correspond OSD pop up when switching status by hot keys. Make sure Vantage/Legion Space/Legion Zone UI status should be same with OSD. Power LED and power plan follow mode switched: Performance:LED:Red;Power plan:Legion performance mode; Balance:LED:White; Power plan:Legion Balance mode; Quiet:LED:Blue; Power plan:Legion Quiet mode *Power LED color please refer project UX spec *Legion Power plan if support please refer project Fn+Q spec. Custom Mode(The FN+Q hotkey cannot be switched to custom mode):LED:Purple; *Power LED color please refer project UX spec
3. Repeat step2 for 10 times
Mode can be switched correctly
Vantage/Legion Space/Legion Zone UI
Note: Legion Zone is only for SC OS. There have 4 modes in Legion Zone: Performance, Balance, Quiet, and Custom Mode. There have 4 modes in Vantage: Performance, Balance, Quiet, and Custom Mode.There have 4 modes in Legion Space: Performance, Balance, Quiet, and Custom Mode.
1. Launch Vantage /Legion Space/Legion Zone Thermal mode UI
2. Switch Thermal mode by click it. Note:FN+Q 7.0 and Later will not be linked to the Power Plan, so the Power Plan does not need to be checked.

Custom Mode: LED: Purple; You can swtich to Custom mode when using a shipping or "Work with limitation" adapter. You cannot enter into Custom mode when using a "Not support" adapter. You cannot enter into Custom mode on DC mode.
3. Repeat step2 for 10 times
Mode can be switched correctly
